au.org.intersect.dms.wn.impl
Class JobTracker

java.lang.Object
  au.org.intersect.dms.wn.impl.JobTracker

public class JobTracker
extends Object

Class to hold the scope and track progress of a copy job. We cancel a job by throwing an exception from within this object (via an aspect advice on some methods).
When multi-threading gets introduced, this class needs to be reviewed. At the moment, the only field accessed from several thread is cancelJob - but it's not critical, so we don't synchronize methods reading it (although some care was put into jobException as noted below).
